 in front of me at the last second the cast finished. I was gonna finish off some damn ranger that was hill/water bugging in POV. For the record, it killed the shaman, though obviously that was not what I'd intended. It looked like something from a 3 Stooges movie.<br>
<br>
While FOT has an insanely high resist rate in PVP, it's range has its uses in certain scenarios, particularly against rangers on open terrain who like to bow kite or do hit and runs.<br>
<br>
Now, if we had bolt animations fixed, my own friends would have known to stay the hell away from me when I'm casting, but I suppose that's too much to hope for.<br>
<br>
----<br>
<br>
On a similar note, this morning I was PVPing in Storms against a Shaman (who are damn hard to finish off with the new Torpor btw). Along comes a manaburn wizy so I had to disengage and get out of range a bit.<br>
<br>
The wizy gets on his horse and gives chase, while the shaman is still playing with my pet.<br>
<br>
I stopped far enough away from the Shaman that I knew he was going to be licking his wounds for a bit and keeping my pet occupied and focused on the wizy, who was closing fast.<br>
<br>
Started up HOE3... he'd arrived in range of me, ditched his horse and started the MB. My HOEs finished cast first and started beating on his rune. I immediately started the old Sun Vortex which helped in destroying his epic rune + a little damage. <br>
<br>
Somehow the HOEs interrupted his MB and he was fooked at that point. He tried to run but got bashed a few times and stunned. That kept him in range of a second sun vortex putting him down. I think he was a little overconfident and made a mistake. <br>
<br>
I then Summoned Companion my pet away from the shaman so he could be unrooted, unslowed and rebuffed and went looking for him again. Unfortunately, he gated out as soon as he saw me the second time.<br>
<br>
In short, even petless against classes with near instakill abilities, mages are a threat . <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
That said, how about those SKs with 4K+ HTs?  <p><table width=100%><tr><td width=33%><font color=blue><i><b>Sage Svenuce Summonstuff</b></i></font><br>
